</caption>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1258,2137,996,1304]" box="[1259,2057,996,1029]" pageId="0" pageNumber="528">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607325" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6607325" box="[1259,2054,996,1029]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607325/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="528" startId="0.[1259,1272,996,1029]" targetBox="[249,1194,689,1314]" targetPageId="0">• All oceans and some rivers in East and South Asia</caption>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1258,2137,996,1304]" pageId="0" pageNumber="528">• Shoreward of the continental shelf, mostly shallow waters less than 180 m deep; two species occur in deep, oceanic waters (hundreds to thousands of meters deep), and two in rivers.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1258,2137,996,1304]" box="[1258,1713,1193,1226]" pageId="0" pageNumber="528">• 3 genera, 7 species, 11 taxa.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1258,2137,996,1304]" pageId="0" pageNumber="528">• 1 species Critically Endangered, 2 Vulnerable; none Extinct since 1600.</paragraph>
